Description: CVE-2026-48163 - wsrep_sst_rsync.sh: apply safe() to joiner-supplied parameters
 wsrep_sst_rsync.sh interpolated WSREP_SST_OPT_REMOTE_USER and
 WSREP_SST_OPT_REMOTE_PSWD verbatim. A newline in either could splice an
 extra directive into the donor-written stunnel.conf (silently downgrading
 peer-cert verification) or add an extra line into the rsync magic file.
 .
 This patch backports MDEV-39648 (route the rsync interpolations through
 safe()). The safe() helper itself is introduced by CVE-2026-44168
 (MDEV-39413).
Origin: upstream, https://github.com/MariaDB/server/commit/dae315a7b2bf8bd2fd0449467e711e5a2db26669
Author: Hemant Dangi <hemant.dangi@mariadb.com>
Last-Update: 2026-06-16
