Description: Fix CVE-2026-44169 / MDEV-39288 SHOW CREATE ROUTINE does not apply to roles
 In check_routine_level_acl(), the role-branch hard-coded the privilege
 mask to SHOW_PROC_WITHOUT_DEFINITION_ACLS, so an active role's grants
 were checked against the wrong ACL bit when running SHOW CREATE
 PROCEDURE/FUNCTION/PACKAGE. As a result, role grants were effectively
 ignored for routine-definition disclosure decisions, leading to
 incorrect access (the routine body was suppressed even when the role
 held the required privilege). The fix uses the caller-supplied `acl`
 parameter for the role lookup, matching the user-branch behavior.
 Reported by Aisle Research.
 .
 Hunk #2 of mysql-test/main/sp-security.{result,test} adapted for Debian
 trixie: the upstream commit appended the new test section at end-of-file,
 but the trixie source has a trailing `set @@global.collation_server=
 @save_collation_server;` line after the `End of 11.3 tests` markers.
 The adapted hunks insert the new MDEV-39288 test block just before that
 trailing line, leaving the existing surrounding markers untouched. Test
 contents are byte-identical to the upstream additions.
Origin: upstream, https://github.com/MariaDB/server/commit/f279551013d1319f27344080e2c0758f3959cebf
