Description: CVE-2026-44171 - mbstream insufficient path validation
 mbstream (xbstream) in mariadb-backup performs insufficient path
 validation when extracting archive entries. A crafted archive
 containing entries with paths starting with '.' or '/', or containing
 '/../' allows files to be written outside the target directory,
 enabling path traversal (CWE-22).
 .
 This patch rejects paths that could not have been written by
 mariadb-backup by adding a guard at the top of file_entry_new().
 .
 Note: the upstream commit also adds a binary test fixture
 (mysql-test/std_data/mdev-39408.mb) and corresponding
 mariabackup/xbstream.test additions. The test fixture is a binary
 mbstream archive that cannot be reliably shipped via a Debian quilt
 patch, so only the source-code security fix is included here.
Origin: backport, https://github.com/MariaDB/server/commit/2bbfcb187602613611912238cbb765e6e7caed4b
Bug: https://jira.mariadb.org/browse/MDEV-39408
Author: Sergei Golubchik <serg@mariadb.org>
Last-Update: 2026-06-16
--- a/extra/mariabackup/xbstream.cc
+++ b/extra/mariabackup/xbstream.cc
@@ -313,6 +313,11 @@ file_entry_new(extract_ctxt_t *ctxt, con
 	file_entry_t	*entry;
 	ds_file_t	*file;
 
+        if (*path == '.' || *path == '/' || strstr(path, "/../")) {
+		msg("%s: invalid filename %s", my_progname, path);
+                return NULL;
+        }
+
 	entry = (file_entry_t *) my_malloc(PSI_NOT_INSTRUMENTED, sizeof(file_entry_t),
 					   MYF(MY_WME | MY_ZEROFILL));
