Description: Fix CVE-2026-48165 — Galera Cluster command execution via SST variables (MDEV-39676)
 The wsrep_sst_donor, wsrep_sst_method and wsrep_sst_receive_address system
 variables previously accepted any string and were later interpolated into
 shell commands invoked by the SST scripts. A privileged user could set
 them to values containing shell metacharacters and trigger command
 execution on the donor node.
 .
 This patch ports the upstream MariaDB fix series:
   * 13e6808f — primary fix: validate the three SST variables in
     sql/wsrep_sst.cc against allow-listed character sets and add
     mysql-test coverage (MDEV-39676).
   * a9e2f7f6 — follow-up: re-disallow `SET GLOBAL wsrep_sst_donor=NULL`
     to avoid a regression seen in galera.mdev-28433 (this commit reverts
     the wsrep_sst_donor changes from 13e6808f, so those files are not
     touched by the squashed result).
   * b2050fdb — strengthen safe() in scripts/wsrep_sst_common.sh by
     also rejecting the '$' character.
 .
 The safe() helper and rsync-side hardening (dae315a7 / MDEV-39648) are
 provided by CVE-2026-44168 and CVE-2026-48163 respectively. This patch
 only carries the sql/wsrep_sst.cc validation work from 13e6808f and the
 strengthened safe() check from b2050fdb.
