Description: CVE-2026-44168 - wsrep unsafe handling of parameters
 Introduces a safe() wrapper for parameters interpolated into shell
 command lines in wsrep_sst_common.sh and wsrep_sst_mariabackup.sh
 to prevent shell injection via maliciously crafted SST parameters.
 .
 A parameter is considered safe only if it contains no spaces, single
 quotes or backticks. Affected variables include WSREP_SST_OPT_HOST_UNESCAPED,
 WSREP_SST_OPT_REMOTE_USER, WSREP_SST_OPT_PORT, WSREP_SST_OPT_HOST,
 WSREP_SST_OPT_LSN and WSREP_SST_OPT_SST_VER, which a malicious joiner
 could otherwise use to execute arbitrary shell commands on the donor
 (for example through a peer certificate CommonName containing
 backticks or quotes evaluated by the donor's shell during SST setup).
 .
 Backported from MariaDB upstream commit
 3e3c5d72c8fbff5994edcb43d3cf387628de2d32 (MDEV-39413).
 The only adaptation versus the upstream diff is the comment
 reference in mysql-test/lib/generate-ssl-certs.sh which says
 (MDEV-16266) in the trixie source tree rather than (MDEV-7598).
