Description: CVE-2026-44173 - Fix FILE privilege check for derived tables in SELECT INTO OUTFILE
 MariaDB allowed SELECT ... INTO OUTFILE and SELECT ... INTO DUMPFILE
 without verifying the FILE privilege if the FROM clause contained only
 subqueries (derived tables) or a JSON_TABLE expression. A low-privileged
 user with only SELECT could bypass the FILE privilege check and write
 query results to the server's filesystem.
 .
 Fix: check the global FILE_ACL separately via check_global_access()
 before the per-table SELECT_ACL checks, both in mysql_execute_command()
 and in mysql_test_select() (prepared statement path).
 .
 MDEV-39493 / GHSA-667j-m53j-wpmc
 .
 The companion regression test changes for mysql-test/main/outfile.test
 and the binary mysql-test/main/outfile.result from upstream are not
 included here because the surrounding test scaffolding (cursor protocol
 wrappers, @tmpdir indirection, hex(load_file ...)) was rewritten between
 11.8.6 and 11.8.7 and the result file is binary in the upstream commit;
 the json_table_notembedded test below already exercises the derived-table
 FILE privilege check path that this CVE fixes.
Origin: upstream, https://github.com/MariaDB/server/commit/c0fb8448332972fce3adc176f195a573f9fdc83d
Bug: https://jira.mariadb.org/browse/MDEV-39493
Author: Sergei Golubchik <serg@mariadb.org>
Last-Update: 2026-06-16

